# Project: AI Workflow Playbook

## Tech Stack

- PHP 8.3+ with Laravel / Pure PHP
- TypeScript 5.x
- React 18.x
- MySQL

## Core Conventions

- Use strict typing in PHP: `declare(strict_types=1)`
- All class properties must be typed
- Return types required on all methods
- Use `===` for comparisons (strict equality)
- PSR-12 code formatting

## Architecture

- **Actions/** — Single-responsibility business logic
- **Models/** — ORM models, no business logic
- **Services/** — Cross-cutting concerns only
- **Dtos/** — Data transfer objects (PHP 8.x record types)

## Code Quality

- PHPStan (Level 7+) for static analysis
- Pint for code formatting
- Pest/PHPUnit for testing
- Never commit without running tests

## Git Workflow

- NEVER create commits automatically
- NEVER push without explicit user request
- Use descriptive branch names: `feature/ticket-description`
- PR description: no AI mentions, no stats

## Security

- Never expose secrets in code
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Validate all inputs
- Use parameterized queries (no SQL injection)